
# vi:ft=gitcommit:tw=72:sw=2:ts=2:expandtab:spell
#
# 50-character subject line
# * type: build, chore, ci, docs, feat, fix
#         perf, refactor, revert, style, test
# * scope: depends on repository
# * description: imperative, this commit will...
#
# 72-character wrapped longer description (body)
# * why is this change needed?
# * how does it address the issue?
# * provide links to relevant tickets, articles, or resources
#
# necessary references on footer
# * BREAKING CHANGE: or appends a ! after the type/scope
# * other footer: follow git-trailer format (`token: value`)
#   * Refs, Fixes, Source-link, Change-id, Co-Authored-By
#   * Reviewed-On, Reviewed-By
#
# see https://blog.avm-martin.my.id/2023/06/commits-v1-tldr.html
